{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She would give us the shots, which everybody-- I mean, any time I can remember any of the children, who I still know today, we all remember the shots they gave us in the shoulder, because nobody could move after that for about three days.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "At that time, they had these DPT shots, I guess, for diphtheria and so forth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was--it was painful.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But we-- we-- you know, we were organized into different rooms-- like I was in a particular room in this home with five or six other boys.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My room was room number D.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There were six other boys, all the same age group, and we started forming a real close friendship.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And basically what happened was we started becoming a family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Instead of--instead of being friends, it was more like becoming siblings with the kids in your own room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And that was the same thing for the other age groups, like the 12-year-olds.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Or later on, some older children started coming, who were, you know, 12, 13, 14.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Then, in approximately May of 1939, there was a ship that left Germany from Hamburg, called the St.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Louis, that took approximately 950 Jewish Jews to Cuba, who had gotten visas to enter Cuba.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Well, Cuba refused them, and turned the ship back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I think it's-- it's pretty much-- that's a historical event, which is known, I think, in many of the history books.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But amongst the-- eventually those people, four countries each took one quarter of the ship's population.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And the people-- the kids-- the kids who were disembarked in France, which was one of the countries that took some of the ship's population, most of those people sent their children to the OSE homes.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
